\title{fNIRS: Hemodynamic (4-Channel Hub)}
\taxon{device}
\author{monaduck1069}
\date{2026-04-03}
\tag{fnirs}
\tag{hardware}
\meta{modality}{hemodynamic}
\meta{manufacturer}{PLUX}
\meta{product}{biosignalsplux fNIRS Pioneer Kit}
\meta{sku}{820201013}
\meta{price}{$3,998}

\p{biosignalsplux 4-channel hub with fNIRS sensor. The Pioneer Kit bundles the hub, one fNIRS sensor, charger, and Bluetooth dongle. Single-site prefrontal hemodynamic monitoring via functional near-infrared spectroscopy.}

\subtree{\title{fNIRS sensor}
\taxon{remark}
\p{1 fNIRS sensor (digital, SPI). Dual-wavelength: 660 nm red + 860 nm infrared. Single photodiode detector. Connects to the ground/reference port (not an analog channel). Outputs on virtual channels 9 (red) and 10 (IR) in OpenSignals. 16-bit resolution, 500 Hz sampling. Measures oxyhemoglobin/deoxyhemoglobin concentration changes in cortical tissue at one site. Designed for forehead placement; LED intensity adjustable via API for other regions.}}

\subtree{\title{Remaining channels}
\taxon{remark}
\p{4 analog channels remain fully available for other biosignals sensors (EEG, EMG, ECG, EDA, etc.). The fNIRS sensor does not consume an analog port. Sampling up to 3 kHz per channel, 16-bit resolution, Bluetooth wireless, ~10 hr battery.}}

\subtree{\title{Kit contents}
\taxon{remark}
\ul{
\li{1x wireless 4-channel hub (85x54x10 mm, 45 g)}
\li{1x fNIRS sensor (660 nm + 860 nm, SPI, 100 cm cable)}
\li{1x Bluetooth dongle}
\li{1x medical-grade charger}
\li{OpenSignals software + APIs (Python, C++, MATLAB, Java, Android)}
}}
